  "text": "L-Arginine hydrochloride monohydrate is an organic hydrogen-bonded molecular salt crystal with chemical formula C6H15N4O2+·Cl−·H2O. It crystallizes in the non-centrosymmetric monoclinic space group P21 (No. 4) with unit-cell parameters a = 11.044 Å, b = 8.481 Å, c = 11.214 Å, β = 91.31°, Z = 4. The crystal structure was determined by single-crystal X-ray diffraction at 295 K with an R factor of 3.3% and a density of 1.44647 g/cm3. Piezoelectric tensor coefficients d14, d16, d34 and d36 were experimentally determined using X-ray three-beam diffraction. The crystal is an experimentally confirmed piezoelectric molecular crystal.",
